From: r03_260516_supervisor (backfill on start)
Subject: cmd_supervisor backfills kline_collection before spawning workers

SyntheticBackfiller already handles gap detection — cold start fills
the full 5-week lookback (_LOOKBACK_WEEKS = 5 → 35 days), warm start
fills whatever gap exists since the last stored bar, gaps under 30s
short-circuit. So this is one call, blocking the parent until done,
before pm.start() spawns the live workers into already-current data.

No new imports needed — both SyntheticBackfiller and BybitKlineClient
are already in run.py's optimus9 import block.

Apply with:
    git apply --check r03_260516_backfill_on_start.diff   # validate
    git apply r03_260516_backfill_on_start.diff           # apply
---
diff --git a/run.py b/run.py
--- a/run.py
+++ b/run.py
@@ -304,6 +304,14 @@ def cmd_supervisor(args, db: DatabaseManager) -> int:
         'database': os.environ.get('PK_DB_NAME',     'pk_optimizer'),
         'port':     int(os.environ.get('PK_DB_PORT', 3306)),
     }
 
+    # Backfill any gap between last stored 5s bar and now before
+    # launching workers. Cold start fills the full 5-week lookback;
+    # warm start fills whatever gap exists. SyntheticBackfiller
+    # short-circuits on gaps under 30s, so this is cheap when the
+    # supervisor has been running recently.
+    _log.info('Checking kline_collection for backfill needs before launching workers')
+    SyntheticBackfiller(db, BybitKlineClient()).backfill(args.tp_pk, args.symbol)
+
     # Parent doesn't need its DB while supervising — release it
     db.disconnect()
 
